Around the same time the city was gearing up to welcome the New Year, a 23-year-old woman was attacked inside a prominent mall in East Delhi.The victim has been admitted to a hospital with injuries to the head, while the unidentified assailant is suspected to be on the run.The police said the suspect was captured by a CCTV camera installed in the mall, but he is yet to be identified.Deepika works for a private firm in Lajpat Nagar and lives in East Delhiâ€™s Chander Nagar. She had received a call from her family on December 31 evening asking her to join them at V3S Mall in Preet Vihar.She arrived at the mall by metro and joined her family. According to the police, she was leaving the washroom, when an unidentified youth pushed her back inside and attacked her with a blunt object on the head.When she screamed out in pain, the assailant fled the spot, leaving her bleeding profusely from her head. She was rushed to a hospital and the police was informed.